y, dance history, and the embodied practices of dancers themselves, The Bodies of Others examines the ways in which drag dances undertake the work of a shared queer and trans politics. The book will be of interest to scholars and students working on performance, gender and sexuality, and embodiment.  aDescription based on information from publisher. 0aDrag showszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aDrag showszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aFemale impersonatorszUnited States. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan),eissuing body. 0aTriangulations.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.8783686